  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Executive",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Customer Consultation:</strong> Provide expert advice on curtain, blind, and fabric selections based on interior themes, functionality, and budget.</li><li><strong>Site Measurements:</strong> Visit client sites to take accurate measurements for customized window treatments.</li><li><strong>Sales & Quotation:</strong> Prepare quotations, negotiate terms, process orders, and close sales to meet monthly/quarterly targets.</li><li><strong>Project Coordination:</strong> Liaise with installation teams and suppliers to ensure timely delivery and installation.</li><li><strong>Relationship Management:</strong> Build rapport with homeowners, interior designers, and contractors.</li><li><strong>Showroom/Online Support:</strong> Attend to walk-in customers and manage online inquiries. </li><li><strong>Requirements</strong></li><li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Previous experience in sales, interior design, or soft furnishings (curtains/blinds) is highly preferred.</li><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Strong communication, interpersonal, and negotiation skills.</li><li><strong>Technical Knowledge:</strong> Familiarity with fabric types, curtain styles, and measuring techniques.</li><li><strong>Tools:</strong> Proficient in basic computer skills (MS Office/Email).</li><li><strong>Attributes:</strong> Target-driven, energetic, well-groomed, and customer-service oriented.</li><li><strong>Availability:</strong> Willingness to work weekends or public holidays</li></li></ul><p></p>",
